006package gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.datatype.adapter;
007
008import com.google.auto.service.AutoService;
009
010import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.datatype.AbstractDataTypeProvider;
011import gov.nist.secauto.metaschema.core.datatype.IDataTypeProvider;
012
013import edu.umd.cs.findbugs.annotations.NonNull;
014
015/**
016 * Provides runtime discovery of built-in implementations of the core Metaschema
017 * data types.
018 */
019@SuppressWarnings("PMD.CouplingBetweenObjects")
020@AutoService(IDataTypeProvider.class)
021public final class MetaschemaDataTypeProvider // NOPMD - Used for service initialization
022    extends AbstractDataTypeProvider {
023  @NonNull
024  public static final Base64Adapter BASE64 = new Base64Adapter();
025  @NonNull
026  public static final BooleanAdapter BOOLEAN = new BooleanAdapter();
027  @NonNull
028  public static final DateAdapter DATE = new DateAdapter();
029  @NonNull
030  public static final DateWithTZAdapter DATE_WITH_TZ = new DateWithTZAdapter();
031  @NonNull
032  public static final DateTimeAdapter DATE_TIME = new DateTimeAdapter();
033  @NonNull
034  public static final DateTimeWithTZAdapter DATE_TIME_WITH_TZ = new DateTimeWithTZAdapter();
035  @NonNull
036  public static final IPv4AddressAdapter IP_V4_ADDRESS = new IPv4AddressAdapter();
037  @NonNull
038  public static final IPv6AddressAdapter IP_V6_ADDRESS = new IPv6AddressAdapter();
039  @NonNull
040  public static final UriAdapter URI = new UriAdapter();
041  @NonNull
042  public static final UriReferenceAdapter URI_REFERENCE = new UriReferenceAdapter();
043  @NonNull
044  public static final UuidAdapter UUID = new UuidAdapter();
045
046  @NonNull
047  public static final DayTimeAdapter DAY_TIME_DURATION = new DayTimeAdapter();
048  @NonNull
049  public static final YearMonthAdapter YEAR_MONTH_DURATION = new YearMonthAdapter();
050
051  @NonNull
052  public static final DecimalAdapter DECIMAL = new DecimalAdapter();
053  @NonNull
054  public static final IntegerAdapter INTEGER = new IntegerAdapter();
055  @NonNull
056  public static final NonNegativeIntegerAdapter NON_NEGATIVE_INTEGER = new NonNegativeIntegerAdapter();
057  @NonNull
058  public static final PositiveIntegerAdapter POSITIVE_INTEGER = new PositiveIntegerAdapter();
059
060  @NonNull
061  public static final EmailAddressAdapter EMAIL_ADDRESS = new EmailAddressAdapter();
062  @NonNull
063  public static final HostnameAdapter HOSTNAME = new HostnameAdapter();
064  @Deprecated(forRemoval = true, since = "0.7.0")
065  @NonNull
066  public static final NcNameAdapter NCNAME = new NcNameAdapter();
067  @NonNull
068  public static final StringAdapter STRING = new StringAdapter();
069  @NonNull
070  public static final TokenAdapter TOKEN = new TokenAdapter();
071
072  @NonNull
073  public static final StringAdapter DEFAULT_DATA_TYPE = STRING;
074
075  /**
076   * Initialize the built-in data types.
077   */
078  public MetaschemaDataTypeProvider() {
079    // The data type "string" must be first since this is the default data type for
080    // the {@link String}
081    // Java type. This ensures that when a data type is resolved that this data type
082    // is matched first
083    // before other String-based data types.
084    registerDatatype(STRING);
085
086    registerDatatype(BASE64);
087    registerDatatype(BOOLEAN);
088    registerDatatype(DATE);
089    registerDatatype(DATE_WITH_TZ);
090    registerDatatype(DATE_TIME);
091    registerDatatype(DATE_TIME_WITH_TZ);
092    registerDatatype(DAY_TIME_DURATION);
093    registerDatatype(DECIMAL);
094    registerDatatype(EMAIL_ADDRESS);
095    registerDatatype(HOSTNAME);
096    registerDatatype(INTEGER);
097    registerDatatype(IP_V4_ADDRESS);
098    registerDatatype(IP_V6_ADDRESS);
099
100    registerDatatype(NON_NEGATIVE_INTEGER);
101    registerDatatype(POSITIVE_INTEGER);
102    registerDatatype(TOKEN);
103    registerDatatype(URI);
104    registerDatatype(URI_REFERENCE);
105    registerDatatype(UUID);
106    registerDatatype(YEAR_MONTH_DURATION);
107  }
108}
